This paper is about improving the performance of the Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy (CMA-ES) algorithm through structural modifications. This falls under the category of optimization algorithms, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a self-adaptive genetic algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in evolutionary computing. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the exploration of algorithm structures, which falls under the category of control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the generation of novel algorithms, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
